"title": "8488: tithing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8488: tithing",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The practice of offering to God a tenth of the harvest of the land and of livestock, as holy to the LORD. The idea is also used in a more general sense, meaning offering one-tenth of one's income to the Lord.</p>\n<h2>Tithing was practised before the giving of the OT law</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:18-Gen14:20\">GEN 14:18–14:20</a></strong> <em>Abraham offered a tenth of the goods taken in battle, apparently in thankfulness to God for victory.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:22\">GEN 28:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:1-Heb7:3\">HEB 7:1–7:3</a></p>\n<h2>Tithing under the law</h2>\n<h3>Tithing extends to all kinds of produce and livestock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30-Lev27:32\">LEV 27:30–27:32</a></strong> <em>Cereal and fruit offerings could be commuted to money.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:5-2Chr31:6\">2CH 31:5–31:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:35-Neh10:38\">NEH 10:35–10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:12\">NEH 13:12</a></p>\n<h3>All tithes were paid to the Levites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:21-Num18:24\">NUM 18:21–18:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:37-Neh10:38\">NEH 10:37–10:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:5\">HEB 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>Tithes were to be paid in a designated place</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:5-Deut12:6\">DEU 12:5–12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:22-Deut14:29\">DEU 14:22–14:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:2\">DEU 26:2</a> <em>Tithes were paid in Jerusalem, or every three years in towns where the tithe feast was eaten.</em></p>\n<h3>Levites offered a tenth to the LORD</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:25-Num18:29\">NUM 18:25–18:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:39\">NEH 10:39</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of the tithe</h2>\n<h3>Support of the Levites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:21\">NUM 18:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:4\">2CH 31:4</a></p>\n<h3>The tithe meal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:23\">DEU 14:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A three-yearly gift to the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:28-Deut14:29\">DEU 14:28–14:29</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Tithing of minor items must not lead to neglect of major matters</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23\">MAT 23:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:42\">LUK 11:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>\n<h2>Freewill offerings were made in addition to the tithe</h2>\n<h3>They were given freely</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:3\">EXO 36:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:12-Lev7:18\">LEV 7:12–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:3\">NUM 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:4\">EZR 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps54:6\">PSA 54:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:12\">EZK 46:12</a></p>\n<h3>They were given according to ability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:10\">DEU 16:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:17\">DEU 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:29\">ACT 11:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:2\">1CO 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:12\">2CO 8:12</a> <em>There is no specific command in the NT for the church to tithe, but many commands to give generously and to support the Lord's work.</em></p>\n<h2>Blessing promised to those who tithe</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:10\">MAL 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:9-Prov3:10\">PRO 3:9–3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Failure to tithe and abuses of the tithe</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:8-Mal3:10\">MAL 3:8–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:33\">LEV 27:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:15\">1SA 8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:17\">1SA 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:10\">NEH 13:10</a></p>",
